<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1545,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
Taxonomic remarks: Can be confused in nature with a dark montane form 
<emphasis box="[1050,1118,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">phaea</emphasis>
Dannehl, 1926, of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Thyatira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Thyatira batis</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
which has shorter and wider fore wings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1545,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2847265317" collectionCode="ZISP" collectorName="L. Mlokossewitsch &amp; H. Leder. All" location="Of" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
Nomenclatural notes: The specimens were collected by 
<collectorName box="[828,1042,1690,1717]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">L. Mlokossewitsch</collectorName>
(who was a forester in Lagodekhi) “en grande quantité de Lagodekhi … en Mai, Juin et Août”, and several specimens were attracted to a lamp “à Helenendorf et Koussari” by 
<collectorName box="[488,638,1762,1789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">H. Leder. All</collectorName>
of them should therefore be considered original 
<typeStatus box="[1200,1298,1763,1789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Christoph, 1885" authorityName="Christoph" authorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Thyatira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hedemanni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Thyatira hedemanni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Christoph, H." box="[282,466,1797,1824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" pagination="1 - 262" refId="ref6538" refString="Christoph, H. (1885) In: Romanoff N. M. Les Lepidopteres de la Transcaucasie. Deuxieme partie. Memoires sur les Lepidopteres, 2, 1 - 262." type="journal article" year="1885">Christoph, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03FCDF48915DFFD5F4FE6219097EFDD0:8E8A3885915DFFD4F5B760440CB5F8EB" box="[478,508,1798,1824]" name="Of" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Of</location>
these, only 6 are found in 
<collectionCode box="[813,874,1798,1824]" country="Russia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/vmfx-g997" name="Zoological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">ZISP</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
; 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2847265324" collectionCode="ZMHU, NHML" collectorName="H. Christoph's &amp; European &amp; The &amp; Museums" country="Germany" location="Berlin" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Berlin" typeStatus="syntype">
it is known that part of 
<collectorName box="[1154,1318,1798,1825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">H. Christoph’s</collectorName>
collection had been sold, exchanged or presented by himself to different 
<collectorName box="[847,954,1835,1861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">European</collectorName>
collections. 
<collectorName box="[1096,1140,1834,1860]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">The</collectorName>
most famous among them are the 
<collectorName box="[234,343,1871,1897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Museums</collectorName>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[380,484,1870,1896]" name="Germany" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Germany</collectingCountry>
(
<collectionCode box="[498,582,1870,1896]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/99a5-d0z2" name="Zoologisches Museum der Humboldt Universitaet" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">ZMHU</collectionCode>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[619,691,1870,1897]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Berlin</collectingRegion>
) and of England (
<collectionCode box="[891,980,1870,1896]" country="Libya" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/49nc-28y0" name="Natural History Museum, Tripoli" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">NHML</collectionCode>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1545,2041]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,153,539]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
A specimen from Lagodekhi in the coll. of 
<collectionCode box="[681,762,1907,1933]" country="Libya" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/49nc-28y0" name="Natural History Museum, Tripoli" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">NHML</collectionCode>
was designated 
<typeStatus box="[946,1049,1906,1932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Christoph, 1885" authorityName="Christoph" authorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Thyatira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hedemanni">
<emphasis box="[1086,1312,1906,1932]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Thyatira hedemanni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Christoph, H." pageId="2" pageNumber="147" pagination="1 - 262" refId="ref6538" refString="Christoph, H. (1885) In: Romanoff N. M. Les Lepidopteres de la Transcaucasie. Deuxieme partie. Memoires sur les Lepidopteres, 2, 1 - 262." type="journal article" year="1885">Christoph, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Laszlo, G. M. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Ronkay, L. &amp; Witt, T." box="[259,532,1942,1969]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" pagination="1 - 683" refId="ref6734" refString="Laszlo, G. M., Ronkay, G., Ronkay, L. &amp; Witt, T. (2007) The Thyatiridae of Eurasia Including the Sundaland and New Guinea (Lepidoptera). Esperiana, 13, 1 - 683." type="journal article" year="2007">
László 
<emphasis box="[342,401,1942,1969]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">&amp; al.</emphasis>
(2007: 46)
</bibRefCitation>
. This was a male apparently hatched on 21[.]12[.][18]85: this date is 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1324,1380,1942,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">later</emphasis>
than the date of publication of the corresponding volume of 
<emphasis box="[771,1115,1978,2005]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Mémoires sur les Lépidoptères</emphasis>
(Band 2) in which the taxon description was published. From the dates, this specimen cannot be part of the original type series and therefore this designation is invalid. We are therefore correcting the situation under articles 74.2 and 74.1 of the Code by designating the 
<typeStatus box="[271,374,189,215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">lectotype</typeStatus>
of the taxon 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[525,577,189,215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">here</emphasis>
. We choose a specimen in fine condition (coll. 
<collectionCode box="[1116,1178,189,215]" country="Russia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/vmfx-g997" name="Zoological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">ZISP</collectionCode>
: cabinet 217/drawer 5) which is supplied with the following labels: a small blue circle without any inscription, a small quadrat (so called a Christoph’s label) with wide black frame and Christoph’s inscription in black ink « 
<specimenCount box="[1069,1090,261,287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
| Lagod.» and«22 6 80 | Mlok» on the reverse, and a white rectangle with a printed text «Колл. Вел. Кн. | НиколаЯ | Михайловича» [“Collection of the Grand Duke Nikolay Mikhailovich”]. The specimen is actually a female (tip of ovipositor is visible, and it bears two dried eggs) although Christoph treated it as a male, and is supplied with a red 
<typeStatus box="[1060,1163,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">lectotype</typeStatus>
label and corresponding text: “ 
<typeStatus box="[217,344,405,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Lectotypus</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[350,369,405,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
” and inscription: “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hedemanni Christoph" authorityYear="1885" box="[583,679,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Thyatira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[583,679,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Thyatira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
| 
<taxonomicName authority="Chr." authorityName="Christoph" authorityYear="1885" box="[698,875,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Thyatira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hedemanni">
<emphasis box="[698,821,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">hedemanni</emphasis>
Chr.
</taxonomicName>
| Design. 
<collectionCode box="[984,1006,405,431]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
.G. Mironov | et 
<collectionCode box="[1184,1204,405,431]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode box="[1207,1227,405,431]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. Zolotuhin, 2019”. Another 
<specimenCount box="[251,371,440,467]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">5 syntypes</specimenCount>
(
<specimenCount box="[387,444,441,467]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="male">3♂♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[501,557,441,467]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="female">2♀♀</specimenCount>
from Lagodekhi) kept in the same cabinet drawer 6 are designated paralecto- types of the taxon. They all have the same kind of labels and were collected on 4.6.79, 14.4.79, 10.7.82 (
<specimenCount box="[1336,1380,477,503]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="male">♂♂</specimenCount>
) and 7.5.80 and 22.5.80 (
<specimenCount box="[377,416,513,539]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="female">♀♀</specimenCount>
) according to the inscriptions on the reverses of the labels.
</paragraph>
